  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2025-02-11",
    "date": "2025-03-28T20:41:59Z",
    "text": "Agent Raul Gonzalez Officer Safety Act\n\nThis bill establishes new federal criminal offenses for operating a motor vehicle within 100 miles of the U.S. border while fleeing from a U.S. Border Patrol agent or a federal, state, or local law enforcement officer who is actively assisting or under the command of the U.S. Border Patrol.\n\nThe bill establishes criminal penalties for an offense, including a mandatory minimum prison term for an offense resulting in death or serious bodily injury. Additionally, a non-U.S. national who is convicted of or admits to committing an offense is inadmissible, deportable, and ineligible\u00a0for immigration relief (including asylum)."
  },
